WEBVTT

00:00.008 --> 00:01.909
<i>Previously on "Dietland"...</i>

00:01.911 --> 00:03.244
I can't authorize this surgery

00:03.246 --> 00:04.745
unless you lose another 15 pounds.

00:04.747 --> 00:06.763
Doesn't my insurance cover most of this?

00:06.774 --> 00:08.387
You need to pay in full for your visits.

00:08.398 --> 00:11.502
- Any word back from Malleck Ferguson?
- I've tried everywhere. Nothing.

00:11.512 --> 00:13.521
He's probably on a shoot.

00:15.525 --> 00:16.590
Oh! Hey!

00:16.911 --> 00:18.678
I want you to go see someone.

00:18.680 --> 00:21.848
I think that you could do great,
meaningful work

00:21.850 --> 00:23.349
that could help a lot of women.

00:23.351 --> 00:24.715
And when you complete the program,

00:24.725 --> 00:27.420
I will write you a check for $20,000.

00:27.422 --> 00:29.789
The first step
would be getting off the Y.

00:37.223 --> 00:39.324
I asked for dressing on the side.

00:39.334 --> 00:41.760
But the chef didn't dress it, ma'am.

00:41.770 --> 00:43.395
Where's my warm lemon vinaigrette?

00:47.175 --> 00:49.167
<i>Jennifer was dropping men from the sky,</i>

00:49.177 --> 00:51.269
<i>but none of us knew that yet.</i>

00:51.279 --> 00:54.873
<i>All I knew was, I had a date
with Verena Baptist.</i>

00:54.883 --> 00:57.008
Nothing is off-limits, Plum.

00:57.018 --> 00:59.744
<i>No food, no thought.</i>

00:59.754 --> 01:03.748
The New Baptist Plan actually
isn't about deprivation,

01:03.758 --> 01:06.851
it's about being kinder to yourself.

01:06.861 --> 01:09.187
OK. <i>Sounds</i> good.

01:09.197 --> 01:12.524
<i> It sounded like a woo-woo
version of Waist Watchers.</i>

01:12.534 --> 01:15.226
As we discussed, for this to
work, you need to go off the Y.

01:15.236 --> 01:17.962
That's all the first phase consists of.

01:17.972 --> 01:20.359
When your body's gotten used
to a drug like that, detox

01:20.370 --> 01:23.805
can be... an adventure.

01:24.152 --> 01:25.585
Well, done.

01:26.648 --> 01:28.714
I flushed 'em yesterday.

01:30.385 --> 01:33.645
How long have you been taking Y again?

01:33.655 --> 01:36.314
Nine years... give or take?

01:36.324 --> 01:41.619
OK. So when you've been taking
antidepressants for that long,

01:41.629 --> 01:44.722
the way to go off them is to taper
slowly over several months.

01:44.732 --> 01:47.892
Going cold turkey's not
safe, or pleasant.

01:47.902 --> 01:50.829
I need you call your doctor,
get a new prescription.

01:50.839 --> 01:54.232
We want to start by cutting your
usual dose maybe by a quarter,

01:54.242 --> 01:55.741
see how you tolerate it.

01:57.971 --> 02:00.230
OK. Absolutely, I'll do that.

02:00.241 --> 02:02.471
In the meantime, let's
brainstorm some things...

02:02.482 --> 02:04.342
Verena, can I steal you for two seconds?

02:04.353 --> 02:06.970
It's about you-know-what.

02:07.581 --> 02:09.447
Excuse me.

02:12.293 --> 02:14.018
- Hey.
- Hi.

02:14.028 --> 02:16.616
I see you signed on
for Verena's torture sessions.

02:16.627 --> 02:19.324
Good for you. She saved my ass,

02:19.334 --> 02:21.192
and I came in here...

02:21.202 --> 02:23.962
Barbara, let's not scare Plum off.

02:26.040 --> 02:28.299
<i>You know that line,
"I'd never want to belong</i>

02:28.309 --> 02:30.635
<i>to a club that would have me
as a member"?</i>

02:30.645 --> 02:33.505
<i>That's how I felt about Calliope House.</i>

02:33.515 --> 02:35.773
<i>Verena may have been well-meaning,</i>

02:35.783 --> 02:38.843
<i>but she was also the poster
child for skinny entitlement.</i>

02:38.853 --> 02:44.123
<i>She thinks she gets it, but she's
never been in my extra-wide shoes.</i>

02:46.294 --> 02:48.953
Thank you for your patience.

02:48.963 --> 02:52.357
I know you have no reason to trust me.

02:52.367 --> 02:53.649
So...

02:54.981 --> 02:57.315
here is proof that I am for real.

03:00.408 --> 03:03.801
If you want, call the bank, see that
the funds are there. Be my guest.

03:03.818 --> 03:08.388
All I ask is that you wait to
cash it till you finish the plan.

03:10.084 --> 03:12.143
<i>Alicia.</i>

03:12.153 --> 03:14.554
<i>This was my golden ticket.</i>

03:16.688 --> 03:18.788
Is there a problem?

03:20.895 --> 03:23.321
Should I have made it out to Plum?

03:23.331 --> 03:26.658
No. No, it's...

03:26.668 --> 03:29.093
perfect.

03:29.103 --> 03:32.230
<i>Calliope House was changing my routine.</i>

03:32.240 --> 03:34.499
<i>And while I desperately
needed the money,</i>

03:34.509 --> 03:37.504
<i>I still wasn't sold
on the New Baptist Plan.</i>

