<i>some as... as young as...</i>

34:22.704 --> 34:24.362
<i>As young as 14.</i>

34:24.371 --> 34:26.496
<i>I denied committing these crimes</i>

34:26.507 --> 34:28.232
<i>and hired lawyers</i>

34:28.242 --> 34:30.234
<i>to intimidate and harass my victims.</i>

34:30.244 --> 34:32.969
<i>My name is Malleck Ferguson
and I deserve to die.</i>

34:32.980 --> 34:35.072
<i>In a UNN exclusive,</i>

34:35.083 --> 34:36.841
<i>Jennifer claimed responsibility</i>

34:36.851 --> 34:39.143
<i>for killing 12 men
they call the Dirty Dozen.</i>

34:39.152 --> 34:40.545
<i>They wanted me to make clear</i>

34:40.554 --> 34:43.585
<i>that they chose Fashion Week to
deliver their protest message</i>

34:43.597 --> 34:45.716
because, and I quote,

34:45.726 --> 34:48.351
"The fashion industry dehumanizes women

34:48.362 --> 34:50.221
and fosters rape culture."

34:50.231 --> 34:51.989
<i>The question</i>

34:51.998 --> 34:55.525
is not longer who is Jennifer,

34:55.536 --> 34:58.663
but <i> what</i> is Jennifer?

34:58.673 --> 35:00.598
You don't feel good, Plum?

35:00.608 --> 35:02.066
I was sick.

35:02.076 --> 35:04.235
I'm just tired now.

35:04.245 --> 35:06.104
Seven-fifty, please.

35:06.114 --> 35:07.179
Nice.

35:09.183 --> 35:10.894
You're in such good shape.

35:11.519 --> 35:13.169
What do you do to keep
such a nice shape?

35:13.209 --> 35:14.433
Leave her alone.

35:15.709 --> 35:18.616
You want me to leave you alone, you
probably shouldn't dress like that.

35:18.633 --> 35:20.596
- Your ass is hangin' out.
- Got you on video.

35:25.700 --> 35:28.090
Mind your own business, cow.
No one's lookin' at you.

35:28.101 --> 35:30.450
- Look who's talking, jerk!
- Crawl back under your rock!

35:30.605 --> 35:33.564
He was here last week doing the
same thing. This has to stop.

35:33.574 --> 35:36.234
- It's not OK.
- Jerk.

35:36.244 --> 35:38.870
I just can't decide

35:38.880 --> 35:41.873
do I call Stanley or text Abra?

35:41.883 --> 35:44.442
If Jennifer would threaten anyone at UNN

35:44.452 --> 35:46.878
or Austen Media, you know
I would have called you.

35:46.888 --> 35:48.746
<i>And</i> the police.

35:48.756 --> 35:50.414
Unless it made a better story not to.

35:50.424 --> 35:52.825
Please don't.

35:55.062 --> 35:57.221
Fine. Have me fired.

35:57.231 --> 35:59.657
Have Stanley shut down
the whole station.

35:59.667 --> 36:01.125
Jeremiah, it's Ms. Montgomery.

36:01.135 --> 36:02.960
Please wake Stanley for me.

36:02.970 --> 36:05.237
- There's...
- I'm sorry.

36:06.440 --> 36:09.241
I was wrong. OK?

36:14.982 --> 36:17.108
Excuse me, false alarm.

36:17.118 --> 36:19.485
Tell Stanley we can speak tomorrow.

36:21.189 --> 36:23.022
I want your source.

36:25.960 --> 36:27.952
Kitty, if... if I do that...

36:27.962 --> 36:30.288
You might save thousands of lives.

36:30.298 --> 36:33.758
Jennifer's done. It's old news already.

36:33.768 --> 36:35.860
Oh, really?

36:35.870 --> 36:38.529
Jennifer will be yesterday
before tomorrow.

36:38.539 --> 36:40.698
Nothing ever sticks anymore.

36:40.708 --> 36:42.834
You get five minutes of outrage,

36:42.844 --> 36:44.202
three minutes of fear,

36:44.212 --> 36:45.870
and then everyone switches over

36:45.880 --> 36:47.939
to some cute goat video

36:47.949 --> 36:49.996
and it's "What were we talking about?"

36:51.019 --> 36:52.677
Jennifer's different.

36:52.687 --> 36:54.879
Mark my words.

36:54.889 --> 36:57.215
They won't stop until

36:57.225 --> 36:59.684
they believe they've freed
women from oppression

36:59.694 --> 37:00.893
once and for all.

37:02.396 --> 37:04.355
And that's never gonna happen.

37:04.365 --> 37:07.733
Men would rather destroy the
world than let us rule it.

37:15.631 --> 37:17.935
I'm glad you're not a cop anymore, Dad.

37:17.946 --> 37:19.576
It's too dangerous.

37:21.193 --> 37:23.894
She's worried about Jennifer.

37:28.867 --> 37:30.567
So what did you guys see?

37:32.104 --> 37:34.571
See the video of the guys confessing?

37:38.143 --> 37:40.969
What if Jennifer makes a mistake...

37:40.979 --> 37:43.572
and she kills somebody good? Like <i> you.</i>

37:43.582 --> 37:46.375
Nothin' is gonna happen to me.

37:46.385 --> 37:48.143
Do you still have a gun?

37:50.289 --> 37:51.446
Mama!

37:51.456 --> 37:53.382
What are we celebrating?

37:53.392 --> 37:55.592
- I needed a little sugar.
- Mmm.

37:57.229 --> 37:59.596
Mmm. Caramel. Yum.

38:00.799 --> 38:02.791
Go wash up.

38:02.801 --> 38:06.136
Only Harry Potter.
No computer before bed.

38:17.649 --> 38:20.075
- What's wrong?
- I know money's tight,

38:20.085 --> 38:21.677
but I don't like you workin' doubles.

38:21.687 --> 38:24.313
Well, it isn't forever, baby.

38:24.323 --> 38:26.356
I'm better when I'm busy.

38:27.826 --> 38:30.160
It charges me up. Ya know?

38:45.310 --> 38:47.177
What the hell, Nicky?

38:48.973 --> 38:51.068
- I'm sorry.
- What if somebody sees it?

38:51.079 --> 38:53.580
These women won't open up to you
if they think you're married.

38:53.591 --> 38:57.946
You know I'm superstitious.
You're right. I'm sorry.

38:57.956 --> 39:00.373
How come you always
make me feel like a bully?

39:00.384 --> 39:02.350
Marissa, can we not do this tonight?

39:06.939 --> 39:08.072
Whatever.

39:15.796 --> 39:19.056
So... how's the case going?

39:19.066 --> 39:23.160
It's good. I might have
found an informant.

39:23.170 --> 39:26.096
Yeah? What's her name?

39:26.106 --> 39:27.998
<i>Her name was Plum.</i>

39:28.008 --> 39:31.068
<i>And while she'd been away
on a quick hallucination,</i>

39:31.078 --> 39:33.671
<i>the whole world seemed
to have lost its mind.</i>

39:35.950 --> 39:38.642
- I'm calling the cops!
<i>- It's us, honey!</i>

39:38.652 --> 39:40.752
<i>Open the door, Plum.</i>

39:42.656 --> 39:45.282
- Mom?
- Ohh!

39:45.292 --> 39:47.751
Oh, thank God you're OK!

39:47.761 --> 39:50.654
- What are you doing here?
- She drove all night from St. Louis.

39:50.664 --> 39:52.690
What were you doing in St. Louis?

39:52.700 --> 39:55.092
My plane was grounded,
then I got a rental.

39:55.102 --> 39:57.528
Steven told me about
your withdrawal drama.

39:57.538 --> 39:59.964
It was the only way
to stop her from calling 911.

39:59.974 --> 40:03.267
- Why?
- The phone calls, baby.

40:03.277 --> 40:05.135
You said you started modeling,

40:05.145 --> 40:07.471
that Benny the Bengal Tiger
was a good kisser...

40:07.481 --> 40:09.306
I thought you were
having a psychotic break.

40:09.316 --> 40:10.449
I didn't want you to worry.

40:10.460 --> 40:13.449
- You could have died.
- Please don't exaggerate, Mom.

40:13.460 --> 40:15.878
Shit, shit, shit, shit!

40:15.889 --> 40:18.949
This Verena woman, what's that about?

40:18.959 --> 40:20.951
Who pays somebody that kind of money...

40:20.961 --> 40:23.053
- You told her about Verena.
- Can you blame me?

40:23.063 --> 40:24.722
- This is so typical...
- Enough. Enough.

40:24.732 --> 40:26.357
We all did what we did,

40:26.367 --> 40:28.792
but it sounds like you're
joining a cult or something.

40:28.802 --> 40:30.527
- I mean...
- Damnit!

40:30.537 --> 40:31.974
What kind of therapist bribes you

40:31.985 --> 40:34.339
and then forces you to go off
doctor-prescribed medication?

40:34.350 --> 40:36.699
She didn't! Verena wanted
me to get <i> more</i> pills.

40:36.710 --> 40:38.849
- She feels guilty because her mother was...
- Steven told me.

40:38.860 --> 40:39.931
That's not the point.

40:39.942 --> 40:41.904
You shouldn't be getting
the surgery anyway.

40:41.915 --> 40:44.975
There's no reason to let Verena
torture you for money.

40:44.985 --> 40:46.644
You're beautiful the way you are,

40:46.654 --> 40:48.646
and you have a good life, Plum.

40:48.656 --> 40:50.914
Things at work are finally
starting to work out...

40:50.924 --> 40:53.158
Stop. Just stop. Please.

40:55.095 --> 40:58.255
I get it. You love me, you were scared.

40:58.265 --> 41:00.991
I get it, I'm sorry.
But I'm not a child.

41:01.001 --> 41:03.093
And I'm not a moron.

41:03.103 --> 41:05.062
We don't think that.

41:05.072 --> 41:07.398
I don't want to be a glamazon.

41:07.408 --> 41:09.166
I just want to get on an airplane

41:09.176 --> 41:11.902
and not have to apologize
to the person I sit next to.

41:11.912 --> 41:15.039
I want to go to a bar and get
hit on by some bald guy,

41:15.049 --> 41:18.509
and I want us to argue about whether
said bald guy is actually into me

41:18.519 --> 41:20.177
or whether he just wants to get laid.

41:20.187 --> 41:23.447
- I know.
- You don't, Steven!

41:23.457 --> 41:24.890
You can't!

41:31.532 --> 41:33.724
Going off Y, I got my feelings back,

41:33.734 --> 41:35.793
and it made me remember why
I wanted 'em gone.

41:35.803 --> 41:37.361
Don't say that, honey.

41:37.371 --> 41:40.130
No, no. What I realized was,

41:40.140 --> 41:44.068
I don't hate myself...
The <i> world</i> hates me.

41:44.078 --> 41:45.703
For being like this.

41:45.713 --> 41:48.072
Every day I walk around in this skin,

41:48.082 --> 41:50.441
people look at me
like I have the plague.

41:50.451 --> 41:52.417
They act like I'm a <i> stain.</i>

41:53.487 --> 41:56.714
They stare and laugh and yell,

41:56.724 --> 42:00.884
and worst of all, they tell me
I have such a pretty face...

42:00.894 --> 42:03.954
and then they lecture me
on how I can fix my body,

42:03.964 --> 42:05.823
because how I am is wrong.

42:05.833 --> 42:08.158
- That's not true.
- It <i> is</i> true.

42:08.168 --> 42:10.602
You can't see it because you love me.

42:12.106 --> 42:14.072
But if this is it,

42:14.091 --> 42:16.417
if this is my life,

42:16.428 --> 42:18.666
if this is my body...

42:19.246 --> 42:21.279
I'd rather be dead.

